# Regression: plain `key: value` fields whose flat width exceeds
# the available budget break before the value, with the value
# indented one level deeper than the key. AllowRowBreak gates this
# behaviour: only field rows opt in, so list/call/chain rows with
# trailing comments aren't subject to the break.
#
# longestAlignedPrefix segments around AllowRowBreak rows whose
# own flat width exceeds avail, so each overflowing field becomes
# its own single-row segment. renderTableSegment's breakRow path
# then fires per segment (preconditions: !info[0].broken, Raw=nil,
# AllowRowBreak, MergedFirstCell=nil, len(cells)>=2, !cells[1]
# .canBreak, totalFlat > avail) and emits "\n\t" before cell 1.
# Setting AllowRowBreak=false on the field row, OR removing the
# breakRow block from renderTableSegment, OR removing the
# AllowRowBreak segmentation guard in longestAlignedPrefix's
# rowFits, makes both fields render as single overflowing lines.
#
# Only the norelpos pass exercises the break: in the relpos pass
# the file is wrapped in an infinite-width scope (parsed-mode), and
# rowFits's AllowRowBreak guard skips itself under infinite width so
# the user's layout is preserved.
-- config --
width: 20
-- in.cue --
aaaaaaaaaaaaaaa: bbbbbbbbbbbbbbb
aaaaaaaaaaaaaac: bbbbbbbbbbbbbbd
-- out/relpos --
aaaaaaaaaaaaaaa: bbbbbbbbbbbbbbb
aaaaaaaaaaaaaac: bbbbbbbbbbbbbbd
-- out/norelpos --
aaaaaaaaaaaaaaa:
	bbbbbbbbbbbbbbb
aaaaaaaaaaaaaac:
	bbbbbbbbbbbbbbd
